160 161 :M
f0_18 sf
-.066(Model-Based Object Recognition)A
187 185 :M
f0_16 sf
-.086(A Survey of Recent Research)A
277 210 :M
f0_10 sf
-.25(\312\312\312)A
251 226 :M
-.063(Arthur R. Pope)A
233 242 :M
-.03(Technical Report 94\32004)A
254 258 :M
-.054(January 1994)A
256 401 :M
f1_10 sf
-.029(Abstract)A
59 430 :M
f0_10 sf
-.009(We survey the main ideas behind recent research in model-based object recognition. The survey covers)A
59 450 :M
-.003(representations for models and images and the methods used to match them. Perceptual organization, the)A
59 470 :M
-.005(use of invariants, indexing schemes, and match verification are also reviewed. We conclude that there is)A
59 490 :M
-.004(still much room for improvement in the scope, robustness, and efficiency of object recognition methods.)A
59 510 :M
-.009(We identify what we believe are the ways improvements will be achieved.)A
endp
