90 538 :M
f0_10 sf
-.008(system, Ettinger \(1987\) uses both a structure hierarchy for dividing object models into subparts, and a scale)A
90 558 :M
-.005(hierarchy for representing each subpart at various levels of detail. Before recognition, models are decom)A
508 558 :M
(-)S
90 578 :M
-.004(posed automatically into subparts according to heuristics that look for \322necks\323 and other shape properties.)A
90 598 :M
f0_9 sf
-.009(SAPHIRE)A
f0_10 sf
-.006(\325s recognition algorithm first recognizes the subparts in an image and then recognizes objects in)A
90 618 :M
-.007(terms of those subparts \(i.e., treating entire subparts as features\). When recognizing a subpart, it first uses)A
90 638 :M
-.005(coarse features and then proceeds to finer ones. By decomposing the search in these ways, a large search is)A
90 658 :M
-.007(replaced by numerous smaller searches, altogether requiring less computation. The idea of decomposing the)A
90 678 :M
-.006(search according to a structure hierarchy and using that hierarchy to guide a bottom-up process is also)A
90 698 :M
